items.summary: Breakfast Spot connoisseurs tend to come here

items.text: I don't care if you get the beloved blueberry pancakes or not, but the must have here is the SUGAR-CURED BACON!
Pancakes that are worth the five-hour wait on a Saturday, but if you go during the week you just might beat the crowd...
Could this be the best brunch in NYC?  Expect a long, but worth it, wait.  Then devour an order of the Pear Waffles – a seasonal special!
Our Readers' Choice WINNER for Best Brunch. We dare you stay away from their dessert cart of chocolate cake and muffins.
Avoid two-hour brunch lines by ordering the stack of blueberry pancakes for dinner.
Try the Blueberry Pancakes and spot it on Foodspotting!
The Best Pancake in town, hands down, although the waiting time for brunch will make you go nuts.
Maple butter that comes with french toast & pancakes will make you feel feelings.
You'll likely have to wait a while to get a seat here around brunch time so when you do sit down, don't leave without getting their unbelievable blueberry pancakes and sugar cured bacon!
Gansevoort Recommended. Order the pancakes!
Go to Clinton Street Baking Co. for dinner and order the blueberry pancakes. No line!
Try the Country Breakfast and spot it on Foodspotting!
don't leave without tryig the sugar cured bacon!
...this place is amazing.  They've got the best pancakes in the world, first off, not to mention the rest of the menu!!
The tip list on foursquare is longer than the wait. You might finish reading by the time a table opens up!
Try not to look like a crazed animal while devouring their Blueberry Pancakes with Warm Maple Butter. Go on a weekday for a shorter (if any) line.
I want to bathe in the southern breakfast; it's that good.
The blueberry pancakes at this NY restaurant have people lining up on weekend mornings. Try making them at home. Find a recipe for the lip-smacking goodie in JUST MARRIED AND COOKING.
Get up early (to avoid the wait) in the morning and try the sugar-cured bacon
Sugar Cured Bacon IS YOUR GOD. Worship it accordingly and offer it praise.
